        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "### Regarding Your Query\n\nThe NIST SRD-46 (Critically Selected Stability Constants of Metal Complexes) database is a comprehensive resource for aqueous-phase stability constants, but there are two issues with your request:\n\n1. **No specific metal–ligand system was specified.** The database contains stability constants for thousands of metal–ligand combinations. To look up data, I need to know which metal(s) and ligand(s) you're interested in (e.g., Cu²⁺ with EDTA, Fe³⁺ with oxalate, etc.).\n\n2. **Pressure is not a standard search parameter.** SRD-46 indexes measurements primarily by:\n\n   | Condition | Typical Range |\n   |-----------|--------------|\n   | Temperature | 0–300 °C (most data near 25 °C) |\n   | Ionic strength | 0–6 mol/L |\n   | Electrolyte | e.g., NaClO₄, KNO₃ |\n   | Solvent | mostly water |\n\n   **Pressure is generally not recorded** as an explicit variable. At 200 °C, aqueous measurements would typically be conducted under autogenous (saturation) pressure (~15.5 bar) or in sealed vessels, but the pressure value itself is rarely cataloged.",
