        "text": "### A Note on High-Temperature Data\n\nStability constant measurements at 200 °C are relatively rare compared to the standard 25 °C reference. Systems that *do* have high-temperature data tend to involve geochemically or industrially important species (e.g., metal chlorides, hydroxides, sulfates relevant to hydrothermal systems).\n\n**Please specify the metal–ligand system you're interested in, and I'll search right away!**",
